column8: Purple Squirrel is a protocol designed for creators and platforms to create membership experiences. Purple Squirrel’s goal is to easily implement and dramatically increase user experiences from “users” to “members,” creating a much healthier monetization environment for the web.  There are several interdependent components of Purple Squirrel.  These are:  ● Purple Squirrel Labs:  The core team that created and currently maintains Purple Squirrel Protocol.  ● Purple Squirrel Protocol:  A suite of upgradable smart contracts that create memberships as NFTs.  ● The Purple Squirrel Network:  A community of creators, distributors, and consumers who share ownership of Purple Squirrel Protocol through their contributions using the protocol.  ● Purple Squirrel DAO: A decentralized organization of token holders who govern and control Purple Squirrel Protocol.  ● Purple Squirrel Toolbox:  Front-end convenience applications built by Purple Squirrel Labs to further sustainable innovation on Purple Squirrel Protocol.  Purple Squirrel Labs:  created Purple Squirrel Protocol to provide an open, shared infrastructure for memberships that removes friction, increases conversion, enables scale, reduces costs, and evolves the web from a business model built on attention toward one based on membership.  Purple Squirrel Protocol belongs to the Purple Squirrel Network,  not Purple Squirrel Labs and is governed by the Purple Squirrel DAO.  We aim for Purple Squirrel Protocol to be the primitive for every membership, both online and offline, around the globe. Together, we will create an internet owned and monetized by creators and their supporters.

column8: DRONEQUBE is an innovative agri-tech startup that specializes in autonomous drone technology for precision agriculture, with a focus on viticulture. Leveraging advanced data analytics, AI-driven anomaly detection, and precision spraying techniques, DRONEQUBE aims to address critical challenges faced by the wine-growing industry. These challenges include the impacts of global warming on vineyard yields, the rising costs associated with an aging agricultural workforce, and the increasing residues on food from traditional farming practices. The company's technology suite includes a state-of-the-art AgriData Archive for climate-adaptive viticulture, which records and integrates vegetation indices, thermal data, and weather sensor information to provide comprehensive vineyard insights. DRONEQUBE's 3D Virtual Vineyard platform utilizes drone data to create detailed vineyard maps for virtual inspections, enabling early problem detection and targeted interventions. Their flagship offering, the Smart Spray & Autonomous Refill System, embodies precision agriculture by autonomously applying and tracking agrochemicals with minimal waste, thus optimizing resource usage and improving crop yields. DRONEQUBE’s technology promises a significant reduction in agrochemical and water consumption, with a consequent increase in yield, aligning with sustainability goals and the need for high-efficiency agricultural practices. The potential of DRONEQUBE's solutions to revolutionize viticulture is underscored by their robust financial model, which anticipates substantial savings for the industry through reduced labor costs and increased efficiency. The startup’s alignment with key sustainability goals such as climate action, zero hunger, and industry innovation further positions it as a forward-thinking player in the agri-tech space.

DecentraX is building a blockchain & DEX based off of custom hardware technology. The DecentraX (DCX) blockchain is being built from the ground up by designing the proprietary hardware that runs the network around blockchain needs. To-date blockchains are built on top of existing hardware that was not necessarily designed to effectively operate for this industry. Minmaster Chips are designed from the ground up around processing hashing algorithms, to effectively allow for increased Transactions Per Second (TPS). The goal for the DCX team will be to meet and exceed 1,000,000 TPS on the DCX Network. The blockchain will grow out with each new project that is adopted into the DCX Network, starting with a Decentralized Exchange (DEX) that will aim to resolve ease-of-use and liquidity problems seen with the options currently available to the market. DCX will act as the gas of the exchange, as every swap that occurs will be paid for in DCX. The DecentraX team believes that DEX trading is the future and will free projects and investors from the chains seen with centralized exchanges.

DeployHub’s mission is to balance the risk of consuming open-source software with the need for rapid development and deployment. DeployHub inventories and fortifies the software supply chain, providing the needed fast response insights when a cyber attack hits. DeployHub’s core is based on Ortelius.io, an open-source project incubating at the Continuous Delivery Foundation (Linux Foundation). Unique to the DeployHub offering is its ability to gather and centralize DevOps and Security intelligence, with snapshots and versioning for each change made across the software supply chain. DeployHub defines an organization's software supply chain by aggregating critical data, like SBOMs, to the higher organizational levels, creating new versions of the supply chain data each time an underlying component changes. DeployHub's Open Source Supply Chain Security Platform eliminates confusion about the pieces of software your teams are consuming, supporting a rapid response to software supply chain attacks.

column8: Paddle is a mobile application specifically designed for sharing music with friends. In the digital age of the twenty-first century, it’s no secret that social media and music streaming are enormous and rapidly growing industries. Paddle is designed like a typical social media platform with the ability to follow other users, like and share posts, and customize a profile, however, rather than posting pictures or captions, Paddle allows users to share songs. Whether it’s one of their favorite songs or a new song they discovered, Paddle offers a convenient platform for friends to share and discover music with each other. People take pride in their music tastes and love sharing the music they discover with their friends. Thanks to music streaming services, exploring music has become easier than ever. The problem is that a convenient, virtual platform for sharing music doesn’t exist. While you can text your friend the link to a song or post a small section of a song on your Instagram story, texting was designed for texting and Instagram was designed for sharing pictures. It seems that a mobile application specifically designed for sharing music will inevitably be created, and when it is, its growth potential will be massive. Our team understands that the time to create an app like Paddle is now and only now.
